other_tests.procedure_name: Drainage of Appendix with Drainage Device, Percutaneous Approach
other_tests.findings: 4+   (>10 per 1000X FIELD):   POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES.  NO MICROORGANISMS SEEN.

No abnormally dilated loops of large or small bowel. Residual enteric contrast material seen within the colon. Excreted contrast also opacifies the bladder. No free intraperitoneal air. New right lower quadrant drainage catheter noted. Numerous surgical clips seen over the abdomen and pelvis. Rounded mineralized densities in the right upper quadrant likely reflect cholelithiasis. Extensive vascular calcification present.
